{"id":"d=origam-topic-3916//p=83063b04c297409db5a5527ba9cea3e3","tags":{"__document_id":["origam-topic-3916"],"__file_type":["text/plain"],"__file_id":["bea8544a57244682a0d19ab5e1874a2a"],"__file_part":["c028338273ac457ba29cd15b42bc839a"],"__part_n":["0"],"__sect_n":["0"],"source":["origam-community"],"topicId":["3916"],"categoryId":["61"],"url":["https://community.origam.com/t/how-to-work-with-the-client-application/3916"],"title":["How to work with the client application"],"imagesFound":["7"],"imagesDescribed":["7"],"imageUrl":["https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/7/777717b12dd9ebfc92e74ffbd2e280c0080e5e95.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/8/8225d2672b2547f1b58d26374a4492a62e01d535.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/5/594dd4613ebbe10c608753e5fcbac6ad3b081613.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/5/5a431050f2bb28017fd50f76b29982dd4de5bfa6.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/3/3405a8217e7abe20ba2b3bae0cf1f71d6526af03.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/e/e77c5f9a44dfce00dd441ca39597ce9cadb209e0.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/0/09b8cbf14306f1725c8c25b83f9b96a76a26ca23.png"]},"payload":{"url":"","schema":"20231218A","file":"content.txt","text":"# How to work with the client application\n\nURL: https://community.origam.com/t/how-to-work-with-the-client-application/3916\n\n@vikter (2025-01-21 15:24:24Z):\n   \n This tutorial will show you how to get into the new application you created as a project in ORIGAM Architect, its content, and basic functions. \n \n [!success]- Prerequisites for further work \nThere are four basic prerequisites for your app to work: \n \n  Have a running database server  \n  Have a running ORIGAM application server  \n  Have a project created in ORIGAM Architect  \n Have a web browser installed \n \n \n Now we will take a look at what the new client application looks like in its default form before you start creating anything custom in it. \n   Opening the application \n If you are running Docker locally as described in our  tutorial , then the address of the application on your machine will be the following: \n  https://localhost\n  \n You have to use the secured protocol (https), unsecured (http) will not work. \n When confirming this direction, you will most likely get a warning because of the HTTPS certificate. To go around this, just click on  Advanced  and then choose the option  Proceed to localhost (unsafe) . \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/7/777717b12dd9ebfc92e74ffbd2e280c0080e5e95.png]\nDescription: The image displays a web browser warning indicating that the connection is not private. It features a red triangle icon and a message stating \u0022Your connection is not private,\u0022 warning users that attackers might try to steal information from \u0022localhost.\u0022 The error code displayed is \u0022NET::ERR_CERT_AUTHORITY_INVALID.\u0022 Below the warning, there are options including \u0022Turn on enhanced protection\u0022 and buttons labeled \u0022Hide advanced\u0022 and \u0022Back to safety.\u0022 The message further explains that the server could not prove it is \u0022localhost\u0022 and mentions potential causes such as misconfiguration or an attacker intercepting the connection. A button at the bottom reads \u0022Proceed to localhost (unsafe).\u0022\n\n\n  \n   Logging in the app \n Now you should see the login page and enter the username and password you inserted when  creating your new project . \n This is the wizard where that happened: \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/8/8225d2672b2547f1b58d26374a4492a62e01d535.png]\nDescription: This interface appears to be part of a user registration process for a web application. The title is \u0022First Web User,\u0022 indicating it\u0027s for creating the initial user account. The instructional text prompts the user to fill in necessary details to access the application. Visible fields include \u0022Login Name,\u0022 \u0022Password,\u0022 \u0022Confirm Password,\u0022 \u0022First Name,\u0022 \u0022Surname,\u0022 and \u0022Email.\u0022 The login name entered is \u0022viktor,\u0022 with \u0022Viktor\u0022 as the first name and \u0022Ter\u0022 as the surname. The email provided is \u0022viktor.ter@advantages.cz.\u0022 Two buttons at the bottom are labeled \u0022Next\u0022 and \u0022Cancel,\u0022 suggesting navigation options in the registration process.\n\n\n  \n This is how the login screen looks in the Google Chrome browser: \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/5/594dd4613ebbe10c608753e5fcbac6ad3b081613.png]\nDescription: The image presents a login interface for an application branded with the logo \u0022ORIGAM,\u0022 prominently displayed in a red banner at the top. Below the logo, there are two input fields labeled \u0022Username\u0022 and \u0022Password,\u0022 each accompanied by a blank space for user entry. At the bottom of the login form, there are two buttons: one labeled \u0022Log In\u0022 in blue and the other labeled \u0022Cancel,\u0022 also in blue. The overall purpose of the interface is to facilitate user authentication for accessing the ORIGAM application.\n\n\n  \n   App overview \n When entering the right username and password, you will enter the application that looks like this: \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/5/5a431050f2bb28017fd50f76b29982dd4de5bfa6.png]\nDescription: The image displays a user interface for the Origam application. The left sidebar features sections labeled \u0022Work Queue,\u0022 \u0022Favourites,\u0022 and \u0022Menu,\u0022 with various subcategories under \u0022Settings,\u0022 \u0022Maps,\u0022 and \u0022Users \u0026 Security.\u0022 Specific items include \u0022General,\u0022 \u0022Map Configuration,\u0022 \u0022Map Layers,\u0022 \u0022Active Sessions,\u0022 \u0022Add User,\u0022 \u0022Application Roles,\u0022 \u0022My User Profile,\u0022 \u0022User Permissions Overview,\u0022 \u0022User Roles,\u0022 and \u0022Users.","vector_provider":"AI.Ollama.OllamaTextEmbeddingGenerator","vector_generator":"__","last_update":"2026-05-01T23:40:20"},"vector":[-0.02000959,0.0055414313,-0.06805064,-0.026506318,-0.011442775,-0.013179146,0.0010103064,-0.036483273,-0.02200914,0.019097878,-0.0063035972,-0.005224027,-0.0035230764,-0.025108784,0.015314837,0.005947163,0.020539222,0.028006874,0.033573255,0.0061826506,0.0063268794,-0.015323493,0.033420555,0.014962626,0.00015554673,0.0047720987,-0.014225167,-0.046069786,0.015269937,-0.020717708,0.011088109,-0.05155327,-0.013889359,-0.028903458,-0.011753718,0.01045875,0.021191366,0.025182288,-0.032247666,0.024980875,0.00326179,-0.023515986,-0.010863643,0.015742604,0.024891956,-0.0682772,0.021012748,0.0051389826,0.03166724,-0.04646403,-0.017068908,-0.0010012928,0.011250458,-0.0456151,0.038592663,0.02746461,-0.013650637,-0.043641787,-0.050461467,0.01849756,-0.030063415,0.00073961477,-0.031657692,-0.032418855,-0.02793261,0.04970408,-0.0034080711,0.008066963,-0.021612152,-0.046527766,0.004481097,0.029882038,-0.08137412,-0.03949909,-0.08291882,-0.016867725,-0.003622663,0.024698341,-0.024763446,0.02593494,-0.001988607,0.025466105,0.0127814235,-0.00072411174,0.017653467,-0.005791325,-0.046663605,0.077321775,0.01905814,0.009014071,-0.034774955,-0.03542104,0.06276381,-0.0424325,-0.020028789,0.013227224,-0.0048244996,0.00019794966,0.03544578,0.04649341,-0.038931806,-0.03616607,-0.033947553,-0.011898839,-0.036601365,0.014195566,0.015653886,0.003905068,-0.0019503611,-0.030723706,-0.0029714562,-0.01926504,0.038129874,-0.035436958,0.0039607505,-0.0024435523,-0.02439968,-0.007567498,-0.037816625,0.01626024,-0.01590992,0.023626532,0.031452436,-0.009525185,-0.0031813513,-0.0026141999,-0.015912425,0.03471084,0.043727912,0.041270565,0.017734734,-0.030555045,-0.017987307,0.001268